### Create Category

Allows an admin to create one or multiple property categories in a single request. This endpoint accepts an array of category objects and stores them in the system.

**Request URL**

``` http
GET /api/categories

 ```

**Request Body (JSON)**

``` json
[
  {
    "name": "Apartment"
  },
  {
    "name": "House"
  },
  {
    "name": "Studio"
  }
]

 ```

**Single Category Example**

``` json
  {
    "name": "Luxury Villa"
  }

 ```

**Data Format**

``` typescript
{
  name: string
}

 ```

**Res type**

{  
"success": true,  
"statusCode": 201,  
"message": "Categories created successfully",  
"data": {  
"categories": \[  
{  
"id": "6bfdccfa-5dcf-417a-8533-a12f66075517",  
"name": "OFFICE",  
"createdAt": "2026-07-16T20:53:25.546Z"  
},  
{  
"id": "4693df66-5fb6-4731-bf2a-b068343dd820",  
"name": "APARTMENT",  
"createdAt": "2026-07-16T20:53:25.546Z"  
}  
\]  
}  
}

**Required Fields**

- `name` (string) — Category name


**Notes**

- Admin can create a single category or multiple categories at once.

- Category names should be unique

### Update Property

Allows a landlord to update an existing property listing. This endpoint uses a dynamic property ID route and accepts partial updates, meaning only the fields that need to be changed should be provided.

**Request URL**

``` http
PUT /api/landlord/properties/:id

 ```

**URL Parameter**

| Parameter | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `id` | string | Unique identifier of the property to update |

**Request Body (JSON)**

``` json
{
  "title": "Updated Modern Apartment",
  "description": "Updated description with better facilities.",
  "rent": 28000,
  "bedrooms": 3,
  "bathrooms": 2,
  "address": "House 30, Road 5",
  "city": "Dhaka",
  "division": "Dhaka",
  "country": "Bangladesh",
  "categoryId": "660e8400-e29b-41d4-a716-446655440001"
}

 ```

**Data Format**

``` typescript
{
  title?: string;
  description?: string;
  rent?: number;
  bedrooms?: number;
  bathrooms?: number;
  address?: string;
  city?: string;
  division?: string;
  country?: string;
  categoryId?: string;
}

 ```

**Notes**

- Only provided fields will be updated.

- The property ID must be passed as a route parameter.

- Only the property owner (landlord) can update their property.

- `categoryId` must reference an existing property category.
